Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @carrot{2} and @parsnip{2} then halve lengthways (no need to peel).
Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots and parsnip onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the #oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn the #tray halfway through.

Place a #pan over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @sesame seeds{1%sachet}, stirring regularly, until lightly
toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the #pan and set aside.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Return the #pan to medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @Irish pork mince{240%grams} and onion for ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Pork is cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet} and @Thai style spice mix{2%sachet} and
fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @hoisin sauce{2%sachet}. Season to taste
with salt and pepper.

Trim the @salad leaves{120%grams}, then thinly slice or tear into bite-sized
pieces.

Just before serving toss the salad with half the @aioli{1%sachet}. Season to taste
with salt and pepper.

Once roasted, toss the roast veg with @honey{2%sachet} and sesame seeds.

> A classic side like honey roasted veg gets an Eastern twist with the addition
> of toasted sesame seeds.

Place the @bao buns{6} (three at a time) on a #plate.

Microwave (covered) for ~{1%minute}. Keep covered until serving.

> TIP: No microwave? Place a large pot with 2cm of water over high heat.
> Once the water is boiling, place a colander lined with baking sheet on the
> pot. Place the bao (three at a time) on the baking sheet, cover and steam
> for 3-4 mins.

Fill the bao buns with the hoisin pork and some dressed salad.

Arrange the roasted honey sesame veg alongside with any remaining aioli.